    "client_msg_id": "838982ee-c22a-474b-98c8-f120503dc9d2",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "*Hello everyone!* :wave:\n\nFirst let me address the important things in life :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye: :\n• programming language of choice: _Clojure_\n• editor: _Emacs_\nCurrent status:\n• co-organising <http://reclojure.org|reclojure.org> conference (used to be in London, now on-line, free, and happening next week, everyone’s invited!)\n• building *Nette: Research OS for the Web* (I’m very, very open to a less cheesy tagline)\n_*Nette*_ is something that I’ve always wanted for myself.\nWay to gather all kinds of diverse types of media (tweet is a medium) on a visual canvas which is also an information system\n-- with each gesture of the UI evolving the system and being remembered.\n\nIt’s focused on expressiveness and agency over information. And eventually being collaborative and programmable.\nMore about powerful ways of seeing/understanding and “doing with information”, rather than producing artifacts.\n\nThe only things that’s public atm is this cheeky teaser, doesn’t explain much, but I’m happy to give a demo to anyone who wants to listen and give feedback…\n\n <https://vimeo.com/640304817/13aaa16679>\n\nLooking forward to hanging out more around here. I would really appreciate any feedback whatsoever :heart:\nThanks!",
